The paper deals with machine learning algorithms and adversarial examples, which are commonly studied in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also addresses the issue of privacy and sensitive information, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of biometric data and fingerprints suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The proposed model involves a Siamese neural network and a generative adversarial network, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
